results.title: Who Am I?
results.description: The Chameleon causes Spider-Man to have an identity crisis; Jack O'Lantern initiates his plan of revenge against J. Jonah Jameson

results.title: Backlash
results.description: While Spider-Man searches for the Chameleon, the object of his hunt is being psychoanalyzed by Kraven

results.title: Kravinov's Revenge!
results.description: Spider-Man struggles to escape the Chameleon's trap before his foe can reach Mary Jane, not realizing that his wife can take care of herself

results.title: The Legion of Losers!
results.description: Spider-Man tussles with a gang of washed-up super-villains out for revenge;  J. Jonah Jameson is attacked by Jack O'Lantern

results.title: Mad Jack
results.description: While J. Jonah Jameson recovers from Jack O'Lantern's attack, Spider-Man fights his attacker outside the hospital

results.title: From the Shadows
results.description: Spider-Man is attacked by Kraven's beasts while searching for Jack O'Lantern; John Jameson undergoes hypnosis to learn why he attacked his father

results.title: Into the Light
results.description: A mentally unstable John Jameson runs wild in the streets of New York; Flash Thompson's drinking problem comes to a head; Norman Osborn becomes the new owner of the Daily Bugle

results.title: Citizen Osborn!
results.description: Norman Osborn reappears and asserts his influence over all around him; a new Kraven prepares to confront Spider-Man; Flash Thompson violently confronts his father

results.title: Son of the Hunter!
results.description: As public opinion regarding Spider-Man shifts following his violent attack on Norman Osborn, Kraven draws the wall-crawler out in the open

results.title: Son of the Hunter!, Part 2
results.description: Kraven questions Spider-Man about his father, the original Kraven

results.title: Son of the Hunter!, Part 3
results.description: Under the influence of Calypso, Spider-Man and Kraven become mindless savages

results.title: Angst!
results.description: Doctor Angst tests the limits of Spider-Man's mental and physical endurance

results.title: Some Thing Goblin This Way Comes (Spiderhunt, Part 4)
results.description: Spider-Man, hunted by most of New York, fights the new Green Goblin for the life of the kidnapped Normie Osborn

results.title: Through the Looking Glass
results.description: Peter dons a paper bag to rescue Grizzly and Gibbon from the White Rabbit ... because no one else will

results.title: Prodigy (Identity Crisis [Part 1])
results.description: Peter Parker becomes Prodigy to rescue the daughter of an ambassador

results.title: Man of the People (Identity Crisis [Part 2])
results.description: Prodigy fights Jack O'Lantern and Conundrum to rescue the daughter of an ambassador

results.title: Goblins at the Gate, Part 1: Survivor of the Big Lie!
results.description: When Roderick Kingsley reveals the existence of a missing Osborn journal, the Green Goblin breaks him out of prison to learn its location

results.title: Mine Eyes Have Seen the Glory
Goblins at the Gate, Part 2: Spider in the Middle
results.description: Osborn cuts a deal with Roderick Kingsley for the missing journal

results.title: Goblins at the Gate, Part 3: Bad Business
results.description: With Spider-Man and Daniel Kingsley as his captives, Norman Osborn exposes the Hobgoblin's game

results.title: A Day in the Life (The Gathering of Five, Part Four)
results.description: Spider-Man goes about his daily routine as Norman Osborn prepares for the Gathering of Five; Mary Jane considers returning to modeling

results.title: The Triumph of the Goblin! (The Final Chapter, Part 3 of 4)
results.description: Spider-Man confronts the Green Goblin after finding Aunt May
